  <h1>Recipe Log</h1>
  
  <h2>Prosciutto wrapped Chicken</h2>
  <img src="C:\Users\Mike\Documents\recipe log IMG-1642/html.jpeg" alt="chicken served with quinoa" width:"360" height:"500"/>
  <br>
  <div id="ingredients">  
    <h3>Ingredients</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>4(6-8oz) boneless, skinless chicken breasts</li>
        <li>8 thin slices(4oz) prosciutto</li>
        <li>1tbsp extra-virgin olive oil</li>
        <li>Fresh sage</li>
        <li>1 lemon</li>
        <li>4tbsp unsalted butter</li>
      </ul>
  </div>
  <div id="directions">
    <h3>Directions</h3>
      <ol>
	<li>Adjust oven rack to upper middle level and heat to 400 degrees. Trim chicken, pat dry with paper towels, and season with salt and pepper.
	    Slightly overlap two slices of prosciutto on cutting board and lay 1 chiken breast in center, fold prosciutto over chicken. Repeat with
            remaining prosciutto and chicken.</li>
	<li>Heat oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until just smoking. PLace chicken in skillet and cook intil lightly browned on both sides, 6-8minutes. Transfer chicken to rimmed baking sheet and bake until it reaches 160 degrees, 10-12minutes. Transfer chicken to platter and cover to keep warm.</li>
	<li>Mince 2tsp sage and squeeze juice from lemon into small bowl. Melt butter in now-empty skillet over medium-high heat, swirling occasioanlly until butter is browned and has nutty aroma, about 1.5 minutes. Off heat, stir in sage and let sit until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in 1 tsp lemon juice, pinch of salt, and 1/8 tsp pepper. Drizzle sauce over chicken and serve.</li>
      </ol>
  </div>
  <footer>Suggested:complete the meal by serving it with sides of quinoa and asparagus or other preferred vegetable.</footer>	
